elements.title: United Nations General Assembly Building
elements.contents: ... that according to one account, planners put a dome above the United Nations General Assembly Building (interior pictured) so the UN headquarters could be funded more quickly?

elements.title: Kai Bumann
elements.contents: ... that the German conductor Kai Bumann was the music director of the Warsaw Chamber Opera, and toured Japan with the company twice?

elements.title: Rubicon
elements.contents: ... that the genetic deletion of the protein Rubicon increases the lifespan of roundworms and female fruit flies?

elements.title: Creekfinding
elements.contents: ... that Creekfinding was inspired by epidemiologist Michael Osterholm's efforts to restore a creek that had been diverted decades earlier?

elements.title: John Jarvis-Smith
elements.contents: ... that when the British government discovered that John Jarvis-Smith was not dead, they gave him a medal?

elements.title: their 2019 football game
elements.contents: ... that the Alabama Crimson Tide's loss to the LSU Tigers in their 2019 football game broke a 31-game home winning streak?

elements.title: Pinwill sisters
elements.contents: ... that the woodcarver Violet Pinwill of the Pinwill sisters was still working on a life-size figure of Saint Peter days before her death in 1957, aged 82?

elements.title: Schiller Woods magic water pump
elements.contents: ... that some regular users of the Schiller Woods magic water pump near Chicago believe that it was covertly blessed by Pope John Paul II in 1979?
